Soma Lending Inc. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) compliance.


The firm Soma Lending has designated Martin Cortez as its Anti-Money Laundering Program Compliance Person (AML Compliance Person), with full responsibility for the firm’s AML program.
Martin Cortez has a working knowledge of the BSA and its implementing regulations and is qualified by experience, knowledge and training.
The duties of the AML Compliance Person will include monitoring the firm’s compliance with AML obligations, overseeing communication and training for employees.
The AML Compliance Person will also ensure that the firm keeps and maintains all of the required AML records and will ensure that Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs) are filed with the Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN) when appropriate.
The AML Compliance Person is vested with full responsibility and authority to enforce the firm’s AML program.

Our AML policies, procedures and internal controls are designed to ensure compliance with all applicable BSA regulations and FINRA rules and will be reviewed and updated on a regular basis to ensure appropriate policies,
procedures and internal controls are in place to account for both changes in regulations and changes in our business.

In this agreement Soma Lending declares to prohibit and actively prevent any money laundering activity that facilitates money laundering
or the funding of terrorist or criminal activities by complying with all applicable requirements under the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) and its implementing regulations.

Martin Cortez, lawyer  
                                                               
